Reasoning: The paper deals with complexity theory and instruction sequences, which are central to the study of computational complexity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses non-uniformity, which is a topic in information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category as well. The paper also introduces a notion of completeness and reducibility, which are topics in logic and proof theory, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) a possible category. The paper also discusses restrictions on instruction sequences, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
